Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:15.04,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.35,0:00:18.72,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.82,0:00:24.72,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.72,0:00:39.50,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:46.28,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.44,0:00:54.22,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.05,0:01:01.62,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.03,0:01:08.73,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.90,0:01:15.37,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.81,0:01:22.01,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.01,0:01:31.99,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.73,0:01:40.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since coming here,\NI have been given the opportunity...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.66,0:01:43.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to enjoy housework\Nfor the first time in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.67,0:01:45.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.50,0:01:50.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have they not come to resemble what\Npeople refer to as "mothers' hands"?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.24,0:01:58.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see that you have no intention\Nof speaking a harsh word to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.92,0:02:03.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was because of my incompetence\Nthat Prince Chagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.42,0:02:08.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come here so that\Nyou could repent your sins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.86,0:02:17.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To this day, I still believe\Nthat Chagum is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.67,0:02:23.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I expect that I appear as a\Nfoolish mother in your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.84,0:02:26.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I simply cannot believe that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.64,0:02:31.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that person would die\Nwithout completing her promised task.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.78,0:02:35.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By "that person," you are referring\Nto the female bodyguard?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:42.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I saw in her eyes an indomitable\Nstrength of will and magical power.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.69,0:02:49.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga, if you wish to repay what\Nyou see as an obligation toward me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.23,0:02:53.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...will you go and verify with your\Nown eyes whether Chagum still lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.80,0:02:58.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you do that, I will be able\Nto live here in contentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.11,0:03:06.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I once believed that a strength similar\Nto hers dwelled in your own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.35,0:03:09.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or was I mistaken in that belief?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.22,0:03:14.19,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 9\NShuga Thirsts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.16,0:03:22.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa! I need some rice pounded!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.70,0:03:25.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.20,0:03:27.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whose kid are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.77,0:03:31.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's your problem? Can't you talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.28,0:03:37.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.31,0:03:40.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.55,0:03:42.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is the old man out?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.09,0:03:44.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I need him to pound\Nsome rice for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.65,0:03:48.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see. So our water mill\Nhad some customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.16,0:03:50.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.39,0:03:51.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.20,0:04:00.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,First, we shall establish a new\Nsteel office which will oversee...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:03.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the production\Nand distribution of iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.01,0:04:05.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only those goods that have met\Nthis office's strict standards...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.44,0:04:07.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...will be allowed to carry\Nthe palace crest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.21,0:04:11.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trade with other countries will also\Nbe conducted through this office.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.81,0:04:16.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Part of the profits will, of course,\Nbe disbursed to the craftsmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.45,0:04:20.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In doing this, I believe we will be able\Nto maintain the highest level of quality...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.42,0:04:23.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and at the same time keep\Nthe craftsmen's morale high.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.96,0:04:26.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, I am convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.16,0:04:29.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have considered every detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.00,0:04:33.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will present your plan at\Nthe next council meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.87,0:04:35.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have no objections, I take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.47,0:04:36.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,None, Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.47,0:04:40.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.75,0:04:44.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.98,0:04:48.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that Chagum's\Npersonal effects are being collected?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.48,0:04:49.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.75,0:04:55.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gakai informs me that you hope to\Nfully lift the water demon's curse...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.53,0:04:58.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...by burning all of these items\Nin the strictest secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.80,0:05:01.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To my knowledge, however...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.40,0:05:05.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it is proving ever more difficult to ensure\Nthat the entire court holds their silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.84,0:05:07.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it is agreeable to Your Majesty...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.84,0:05:10.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...perhaps I might be entrusted to\Ncarry out this duty solely on my own?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.64,0:05:14.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish. I have no objections.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.01,0:05:16.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do as you see fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.65,0:05:24.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He has grown to be\Nan exemplary prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:30.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After Prince Chagum's death,\Nhe seemed rather melancholy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.96,0:05:31.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.06,0:05:35.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He appears to be his old self again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.33,0:05:39.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am certain that is due in no small part\Nto the efforts of his tutor-governor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.14,0:05:46.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your\Ngenerous words, Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.85,0:05:52.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the sign of the great drought\Nwill remain for quite some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:57.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. According to a rumor that\NI accidentally overheard recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.42,0:06:00.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you were relieved\Nas tutor-governor...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.99,0:06:04.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...did you also forget what time\Nour evening duties are set to begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.53,0:06:08.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you,\Nour workload is now heavier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.20,0:06:11.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're setting a bad example\Nfor the apprentices!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.27,0:06:16.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In spite of your zeal for your work...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.31,0:06:18.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...you seem to be overlooking\Nwhat is truly important.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.94,0:06:20.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:22.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that supposed to be an insult?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.55,0:06:25.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And what if it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.48,0:06:28.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who does he think he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.25,0:06:30.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like he knows\Nany more than we do...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.79,0:06:36.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How can they be so optimistic?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.43,0:06:39.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They are so singlemindedly\Nfocused on purification...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.70,0:06:42.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that they have forgotten\NPrince Chagum's sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.04,0:06:48.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop dawdling. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.17,0:06:51.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.04,0:06:54.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing in my quarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.68,0:06:56.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that you two have in...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.88,0:06:59.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those are...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.25,0:07:02.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are going to lift\Nthe water demon's curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.69,0:07:06.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? But we are star readers! That\Nmakes us no better than magic Weavers!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.96,0:07:09.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our orders are to bring all of...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.39,0:07:12.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Prince Chagum's belongings\Nto Crown Prince Sagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.33,0:07:15.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To Crown Prince Sagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.60,0:07:18.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Deliver them to Ichinomiya Palace\Ntomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.20,0:07:19.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.44,0:07:22.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a moment!\NDoing that will accomplish nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.84,0:07:32.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to comfort yourself by\Nlooking at the late prince's belongings?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.65,0:07:35.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should be ashamed!\NHand them over!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.85,0:07:36.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.39,0:07:37.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't!\NWhy, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.42,0:07:38.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please, you must listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.89,0:07:40.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've had enough of you! Give me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.49,0:07:42.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master, let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.27,0:07:51.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.57,0:07:52.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.81,0:08:03.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.08,0:08:05.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.12,0:08:07.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.76,0:08:17.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am sorely disappointed in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.29,0:08:20.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There will be repercussions for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.01,0:08:38.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the master star reader has\Nordered him placed under house arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.65,0:08:41.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is to be expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.55,0:08:45.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, Master Shuga does not\Nappear to be the least bit penitent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.15,0:08:48.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am told that he has voluntarily\Nrelinquished his private quarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.32,0:08:51.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and has instead taken up residence\Nin the star reader apprentices' dormitory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.24,0:09:07.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I presume you have\Nheard what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.81,0:09:09.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just go about your normal routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.52,0:09:21.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga. Crown Prince Sagum\Nrequests your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.06,0:09:24.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The crown prince?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.93,0:09:32.94,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.36,0:09:59.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear detailed accounts of Your Highness'\Ndeeds in every corner of the court.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.66,0:10:03.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They are nothing compared to\Nwhat I am hearing about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.80,0:10:07.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here in Ichinomiya Palace, not a day\Ngoes by in which your name is not spoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.74,0:10:12.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it is hard to believe that these\Nrumors could possibly be about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.54,0:10:18.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With all due respect, Highness, the matter\Nregarding the late prince's belongings...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.95,0:10:21.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It does not strike me\Nas something that you would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.85,0:10:26.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not a day goes by in which\Nsmoke does not rise...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.86,0:10:29.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...from the gardens behind\NIchinomiya Palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.29,0:10:33.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I respected you from the\Nbottom of my heart as a man...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.86,0:10:39.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who was a caring older brother first,\Nand was the first prince second.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.34,0:10:44.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, it seems that\NI was wrong about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.78,0:10:48.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.72,0:10:54.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It happened just inside the forest there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.26,0:11:04.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum had such a keen memory\Nfor facts regarding animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.39,0:11:09.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That day, his sharp eye spotted a bird\Nin flight that he had read about in a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.94,0:11:27.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We remembered the book saying that\Nthis rare bird preyed upon flying frogs...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.82,0:11:32.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we both threw aloft\Nevery rock that we could find.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.29,0:11:37.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it was unable to bear\Nthe weight of the stones...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.06,0:11:41.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It may have been an innocent prank,\Nbut it was a foolish act all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.40,0:11:49.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was Chagum who suggested\Nthat we bring it to the palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:51.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and nurse it back to health.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.44,0:11:54.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The bird was discovered by Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.21,0:12:02.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He scolded Chagum harshly, saying that\Nthe bird's feathers were bad for my asthma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.49,0:12:06.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you remember\Nwhat you did then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.39,0:12:09.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I remember it as if it were yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.29,0:12:14.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Undaunted by him,\Nyou said the following...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.10,0:12:16.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Majesty is being overprotective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.90,0:12:19.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On the contrary, perhaps by showing\Nconcern for small, wounded lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.77,0:12:23.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and by caring for the animals\Nand plants of the outside world...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.54,0:12:26.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...not only will a sound mind\Nand body be nurtured...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.28,0:12:32.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but perhaps those qualities vital in\Nleaders of men will also be cultivated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.88,0:12:36.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the mikado was quite\Ntaken aback by what you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.79,0:12:40.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I am told that it was this incident\Nthat caused the master star reader...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.12,0:12:42.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to make you the\Nsecond tutor-governor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.59,0:12:46.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is no wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.03,0:12:50.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Such was the magnetism and\Nconviction that you had back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.67,0:12:55.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you did just now when you offered\Nme such frank and sincere criticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.92,0:13:08.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No one suspects me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.32,0:13:14.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The courteous crown prince\Nhas the complete trust of the court.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.09,0:13:19.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you did this so that you\Ncould protect his belongings?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.27,0:13:26.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.77,0:13:30.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall leave them\Nin your care, Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.01,0:13:33.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I no longer have need of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.84,0:13:37.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.55,0:13:41.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I was always\Njealous of Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.39,0:13:50.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How I wish I could have seen\NChagum as mikado...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.29,0:13:54.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and you serving at his side\Nas master star reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.97,0:13:58.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Highness...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.44,0:14:04.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What I ought to be doing right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.71,0:14:08.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is not gazing into the heavens\Nlamenting the death of the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.54,0:14:11.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But rather uncovering why the\Nsign of the great drought...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.08,0:14:14.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...has not disappeared in spite\Nof the prince's noble sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.66,0:14:23.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and join those other children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.20,0:14:32.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the perfect chance for you\Nto make some friends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.47,0:14:35.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no real desire\Nto play with children...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.01,0:14:38.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just get out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.62,0:14:50.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.39,0:14:51.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.15,0:14:55.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're racing to see\Nwhose leaf boat is the fastest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.39,0:14:57.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leaf boats?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.60,0:15:02.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want to race, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:05.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You do know how to make a boat, right?\NTry making one yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.37,0:15:08.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he's made some friends already?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:12.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can't say for sure yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.11,0:15:16.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, you don't know\Nhow to make a leaf boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.08,0:15:20.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-oh. Do you think you should have\Ntaught him how to fight first?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.75,0:15:24.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think has the harder job?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.92,0:15:30.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Or a man raising a girl on his own?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.66,0:15:33.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you talking about Jiguro?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.87,0:15:40.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.47,0:15:46.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's definitely harder\Nfor a man to raise a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.88,0:15:51.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The thought of being handed a girl the\Nsame age as him sends chills up my spine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.88,0:15:56.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The difference is that boys will grow up by\Nthemselves even if you leave them alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.49,0:16:03.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, by the time I met you,\Nyou were pretty much a boy anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.16,0:16:08.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I should start making dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.80,0:16:10.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.20,0:16:14.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You said it yourself, didn't you?\NHe'll do just fine on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.34,0:16:19.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, brother! A flying frog!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.28,0:16:21.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.58,0:16:22.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See? Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.78,0:16:31.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, its official name\Nis the Nayoro Flying Frog.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.49,0:16:33.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.29,0:16:39.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Four!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.33,0:16:41.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Five!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.93,0:16:43.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Six!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.03,0:16:45.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.47,0:16:47.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.14,0:16:51.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The frogs are jumping\Nto try to catch their food!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.07,0:16:55.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is wrong to interfere just\Nto play some childish game!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.38,0:16:58.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.25,0:17:07.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, this isn't\Nfun any more. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.29,0:17:46.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Each location's soil samples contain\Nthe normal amount of water...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.43,0:17:48.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are they biting?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.86,0:17:49.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.47,0:17:51.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.00,0:17:56.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is quite a catch you have there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.87,0:17:58.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And look, nothing but big fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.77,0:18:01.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, thank you for saying so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.54,0:18:04.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about the number?\NHas the number of fish declined?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.55,0:18:07.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's no different than the usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.65,0:18:12.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Is there something\Nwrong with the fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.16,0:18:17.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about the\Nvegetable and fruit crops?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.26,0:18:18.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Has the harvest been good?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.49,0:18:22.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it looks like everyone's\Nbeen having a bumper crop.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.71,0:18:33.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.04,0:18:35.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The sign of the great drought is fading.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.45,0:18:40.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This means that the prince's death\Nwas not in vain, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.36,0:18:52.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This one is pretty impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.67,0:18:59.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This one is huge, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.64,0:19:02.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You there, what is it\Nthat you are doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.51,0:19:10.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I spotted these rare grasses,\Nand I couldn't help myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.68,0:19:14.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can make an effective medicine for\Nstomachaches with the roots of this plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.45,0:19:17.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those are fine tools\Nthat you have there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.29,0:19:19.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are they all yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.29,0:19:21.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.12,0:19:23.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind if I\Ntook a look at them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.63,0:19:28.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, these graduations\Nlet you measure things...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.58,0:19:41.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.61,0:19:44.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What were you measuring\Nwith this stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.52,0:19:49.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is there some reason why\Nyou need to investigate the river?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.58,0:19:53.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was investigating something\Nthat will happen in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.92,0:19:59.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To determine whether or not there will\Nbe a change in the amount of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.16,0:20:03.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The amount of water?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.54,0:20:13.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.04,0:20:15.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something important\Nabout that plant?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.54,0:20:18.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, not the plant.\NLook. It's a mantis egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.05,0:20:20.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A mantis?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.38,0:20:24.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This one's just an empty husk now, but\Nthe height at which a mantis lays its eggs...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.62,0:20:27.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...can give you a rough idea of how much\Nwater there will be the following year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.42,0:20:31.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For instance, it's said that when eggs\Nare laid close to the ground like this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.76,0:20:34.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there will be hardly\Nany snow that winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.70,0:20:37.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.07,0:20:40.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that was the case\Nthis year, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.10,0:20:45.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's just an oral tradition among\Nthe Yakoo, but I think it's accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.41,0:20:47.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Yakoo?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.58,0:20:48.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.81,0:20:55.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, I was worried that there\Nmight be a shortage of water soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.95,0:21:00.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming that what you say is correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.59,0:21:03.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the fish in this river are large and fat...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.66,0:21:06.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and the fruit and vegetable\Ncrops are abundant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.30,0:21:08.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.63,0:21:12.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...does that not contradict\Nwhat you just said?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.64,0:21:15.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.47,0:21:21.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Animals gorge on food to fatten up\Nbefore they hibernate for the winter, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.78,0:21:22.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.15,0:21:25.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe what we're seeing\Nis something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.25,0:21:31.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe all the animals,\Nand even the plants...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.52,0:21:36.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...are preparing themselves to survive a\Nset of conditions that will be on us soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.49,0:21:38.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you look at it that way, everything fits.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.46,0:21:41.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is what you are saying, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.53,0:21:46.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That within a year, there is a possibility\Nthat this land will be visited by a drought?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.14,0:21:52.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.14,0:21:58.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, judging from your appearance,\NI think you're from the court.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.61,0:22:01.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So why are you out here\Ninvestigating something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:06.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.49,0:22:09.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! Will you be needing\Nthe boat or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.46,0:22:11.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.83,0:22:15.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I should be taking my leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.76,0:22:18.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?\NWhat is your trade?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.70,0:22:22.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an herbologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.86,0:22:50.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the sign of the great drought\Nhas not disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.60,0:22:55.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...then perhaps Prince Chagum is still\Nalive somewhere, as the second queen said.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.34,0:23:00.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that I must begin my\Ninvestigations again from square one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.68,0:23:13.02,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.02,0:23:20.16,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.16,0:23:25.43,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.43,0:23:32.77,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.77,0:23:47.06,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.06,0:23:56.43,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.43,0:24:03.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.20,0:24:08.34,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.34,0:24:16.72,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.72,0:24:20.92,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.92,0:24:29.16,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.16,0:24:39.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.98,0:24:44.95,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.48,0:24:46.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Worried about Chagum's decidedly\Nun-"common" demeanor...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.11,0:24:48.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Balsa decides to\Ntake drastic measures.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.12,0:24:51.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Soil and Heroes."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.99,0:24:56.99,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 10\NSoil and Heroes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.65,0:24:56.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will the dice that Balsa rolls\Ncome up good luck or bad?
